      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "AMJAAD (5) was strong off a freshen when coming from behind to be 0.4L off the winner at this track and trip. She should be better for that effort and this looks to shape similarly. The form out of her last start has worked out well and she can land the knockout blow. AVOIDANCE (3) was a good winner two back before leading them up in the Grandstand Cup and tiring late. The win two back over this trip rates highly though and he should be able to find the front again here. Can dictate and will take catching. ROCK 'N' THE JAM (9) was sound on resumption off a year-long break and that effort suggested he was back in similar form. Fitter for that run now and his best form is very strong for a race like this. Can return to winning ways without surprising. DUG ANOTHER HOLE (7) is not out of this on recent form and can be handy in the run.",
